President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Michelle Giuda as a Member of the International Broadcasting Advisory Board. Giuda currently serves as the Director of the Krach Institute for Tech Diplomacy at Purdue University and has a background in global public affairs and communications. She previously held positions such as Executive Vice President of Geopolitical Strategy & Risk at Weber Shandwick and Assistant Secretary of State for Global Public Affairs. Giuda has also been involved in various organizations, including the Atlantic Council and Business Executives for National Security. She holds a Master's Degree in Political Management from George Washington University and a B.A. in Political Science from the University of California, Los Angeles. Giuda has received recognition for her work, including being named to the Ad Age 40 Under 40 List and PRovoke Media's Innovator 25 List.